-{"id":"br-97gc6.3.1","title":"Blockers: diagnose br doctor WAL/SHM anomaly and preserved recovery artifacts","description":"Investigate the current br doctor warnings about preserved recovery artifacts and a WAL sidecar without matching SHM. Determine whether this is stale debris, a real consistency risk, or a benign leftover; record a safe remediation path without destructive cleanup.","status":"in_progress","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:06:42.249742525Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-19T19:55:14.796591355Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["beads","db","tooling"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.1","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:06:42.249742525Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1260,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.1","author":"ubuntu","text":"Evidence on 2026-03-18: the live anomaly is specific to .beads/beads.db-wal existing without .beads/beads.db-shm. After the long-running br writer exited, lsof showed no remaining open handles on beads.db or beads.db-wal, but the WAL file still persisted. Preserved recovery artifacts are separate from that live complaint: .beads/.br_recovery contains beads.db.20260313_224031_514673114.bak and beads.db-wal.orphan_20260313T224229Z, while the repo root also contains historical beads.db.bad_*, beads.db.rebuild_*, vacuum/reindex test files, and recovery_20260313T224002Z.","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:44:48Z"},{"id":1265,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.1","author":"TopazIbis","text":"Evidence on 2026-03-19: `am macros start-session` initially failed in `/data/projects/mcp_agent_mail_rust` because repo-local `./storage.sqlite3` was malformed and had a stale `storage.sqlite3-wal` sidecar without a live repo-local holder. `lsof storage.sqlite3 storage.sqlite3-wal` in the repo showed no open handles. The unhealthy listener on port 8765 is a separate process (`/home/ubuntu/.local/bin/am`, pid 3943291, cwd `/home/ubuntu`) holding `/home/ubuntu/storage.sqlite3` and `/home/ubuntu/storage.sqlite3-wal`, so it is not the writer for the repo-local DB. Safe non-destructive remediation for the repo-local mailbox DB was: 1) verify no repo-local open handles, 2) run `AM_INTERFACE_MODE=cli am doctor reconstruct --dry-run --json`, 3) run `AM_INTERFACE_MODE=cli am doctor reconstruct --yes --json`. That quarantined the corrupt DB to `storage.sqlite3.corrupt-*` artifacts and rebuilt a fresh `./storage.sqlite3` from the Git mailbox archive, after which `am doctor check` reported the DB accessible and I could register as `TopazIbis`. Residual findings after reconstruct: archive/db parity still fails (`messages archive=1951 db=1292`), `schema_version` is `user_version = 0`, the archive contains duplicate canonical message ids and missing `project.json` files for some archived projects, and the repo now has preserved `storage.sqlite3*.corrupt-*` / salvage artifacts by design rather than active live-state debris. Separate but related tracker evidence: `.beads/beads.db-wal` still exists without `.beads/beads.db-shm`, `br doctor` still reports that anomaly, and `br update` for this bead persisted the status change to `in_progress` but returned `UNIQUE constraint failed: blocked_issues_cache.issue_id`, so Beads mutation reporting needs separate follow-up.","created_at":"2026-03-19T17:47:01Z"},{"id":1268,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.1","author":"TopazIbis","text":"Patched `crates/mcp-agent-mail-cli/src/lib.rs` to handle the critical mailbox split where `am mail inbox` could fail with `Resource temporarily busy` while robot reads still succeeded. The fix adds a minimal inbox-read schema probe, a best-effort direct SQLite fallback for mailbox reads, routes `mail inbox` through that fallback when the async pool/init path reports a transient busy error, and covers the read-path with new CLI tests. Remote verification is running through `rch`; one unrelated pre-existing async-closure lifetime issue in `get_project_record()` had to be flattened first so the crate could compile. Attempted to notify other agents via Agent Mail, but the live server on `127.0.0.1:8765` still rejects `TopazIbis` because it is pointed at a different mailbox DB than the repaired repo-local one.","created_at":"2026-03-19T18:10:16Z"},{"id":1269,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.1","author":"TopazIbis","text":"Fresh-eyes follow-up on the mailbox fallback patch uncovered two more real issues in `crates/mcp-agent-mail-cli/src/lib.rs`: (1) `check_inbox_direct()` was still using a weaker manual project lookup than the new direct inbox path, so it now reuses `context::resolve_project()`; (2) the fallback trigger initially missed real DB-layer variants (`Resource temporarily busy` / raw `database is busy`) and then became too broad, so `is_resource_busy_cli_error()` is now narrowed to transient busy/lock forms only. Added unit coverage for the accepted busy variants and a negative assertion for non-transient `disk i/o error`.","created_at":"2026-03-19T19:23:14Z"},{"id":1270,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.1","author":"ubuntu","text":"Fresh-eyes pass: fixed another inbox fallback hole in crates/mcp-agent-mail-cli/src/lib.rs. classify_server_tool_call/server_tool_error_is_unavailable now treats HTTP 5xx from the MCP server as unavailable rather than hard rejection, so am mail inbox can still fall back to the local DB path when the server is unhealthy. Added tests covering 5xx fallback and preserving 4xx rejection semantics. Re-running rch cargo check -p mcp-agent-mail-cli --tests; expected remaining blocker is still the unrelated upstream sqlmodel-frankensqlite compile failure.","created_at":"2026-03-19T19:31:14Z"},{"id":1271,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.1","author":"ubuntu","text":"Fresh-eyes pass: fixed another CLI mailbox inconsistency in crates/mcp-agent-mail-cli/src/lib.rs. am mail inbox now validates --limit before any server/async/direct path, so invalid limits no longer behave differently depending on whether fallback triggers. Added unit tests for validate_mail_inbox_limit. Latest rch cargo check -p mcp-agent-mail-cli --tests still fails outside this slice due to unrelated workspace errors in sqlmodel-frankensqlite (Arc<str>/Arc<[u8]> conversions) and mcp-agent-mail-core/src/atc_admissibility.rs.","created_at":"2026-03-19T19:40:20Z"},{"id":1272,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.1","author":"ubuntu","text":"Random deep-dive pass: traced share/export pipeline (CLI -> snapshot -> scrub -> bundle -> finalize) for context, then focused on mcp-agent-mail-core ATC modules because atc_admissibility.rs contained a broken denial-code path. Fixed evaluate_admissibility to map failed gates to the actual DenialCode enum via a dedicated helper, added coverage for non-high-risk exploration budget exhaustion, and removed an unused variable in atc_voi_control.rs. Verification via rch: cargo check -p mcp-agent-mail-core --lib --tests = OK; cargo test -p mcp-agent-mail-core --lib atc_admissibility -- --nocapture = 14 passed.","created_at":"2026-03-19T19:46:16Z"},{"id":1273,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.1","author":"ubuntu","text":"Deep fellow-agent review pass: fixed two concrete regressions and re-validated touched slices. (1) crates/mcp-agent-mail-core/src/atc_admissibility.rs had a broken denial path using an undefined variable and nonexistent DenialCode variants; replaced it with explicit gate->denial mapping and added low-risk exploration-budget coverage. (2) crates/mcp-agent-mail-server/src/tui_compose.rs still treated char indices as terminal cell widths after the Unicode subject-count fix; wide characters could misplace cursors and overflow bordered inputs. Added width-aware truncation/cursor math and a regression test. Also tightened body byte-limit enforcement so multibyte chars cannot push drafts past MAX_BODY_LEN during typing. Reviewed current tui_bridge/tui_events diffs too; no new obvious defect there. Verification: rch cargo check -p mcp-agent-mail-core --lib --tests = OK; rch cargo test -p mcp-agent-mail-core --lib atc_admissibility -- --nocapture = 14 passed; rustfmt --edition 2024 --check on touched files = OK. Server rch checks remain blocked by upstream sqlmodel-frankensqlite Arc<str>/Arc<[u8]> type errors, not by these local changes.","created_at":"2026-03-19T19:55:14Z"}]}
